JSON



Format:key value pairs.
Syntax: compact easy to read/write 
File size : smaller file sizes due to less overhead
Parsing: can be parsed by std javascript function 
Datatype: Natively supports strings,num,booleans, arrays,objects
Schema:


XML
Enterprise grade systems : often used in industries like healthcare,finance, and gov that rely of legacy systems and require high reliebility.
complex document sctructures: ideal for documents that require rich metadata,namespaces,and validation against scrict schema.
specific protocols : still prevalent in tech like SOAP web services which leverage its advanced features like XSLT(transform) and Xpath(quering)

Format:uses tag based tree structure (markup languange).
Syntax:more verbose, requires both start and end tags.
File size : larger file sizes
Parsing: requires a dedicated Xml parser
Datatype: all data is string by default , reqs schema definition XSD,DTD
Schema: mature powerful widely adopted  XSD,DTD for rigorous validation.

